        Ring Signatures
      </h4>
      <p class="text-gray-300">
        Ring signatures solely relying on symmetric-key primitives
        can be constructed by proving an authentication path in a
        Merkle tree in zero-knowledge [DRS18b, BEF18]. MiMC based hashes
        incur a view size of more than a million bits per hash
        function evaluation, which is larger than a LowMC based hash
        by a factor of about 1000. With GMiMC we can change the
        field size and obtain much better numbers.
      </p>
